.TH ACE 1 "2026-07-19" "Ace 0.1.0" "Arcturus Linux"
.SH NAME
ace \- Arch Linux Compatible Package Manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ace
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIoperation\fR [\fItargets\fR]
.br
.B ace
{\fB\-\-deptree\fR|\fB\-\-history\fR|\fB\-\-transfer\fR|\fB\-\-keyring\-init\fR} ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Ace is a drop-in replacement for
.BR pacman (8)
written in V. It supports all standard pacman subcommands with matching
flags and behaviour, plus additional features: dependency tree, transaction
history, one-shot pacman migration, coloured crimson UI, and a native
keyring manager.
.PP
Ace can operate in two modes: native (using
.IR /var/lib/ace/ )
or pacman-compatible (using
.B \-\-pacman
to share
.IR /var/lib/pacman/ ).

.SH OPERATIONS
.TP
\fB\-Q\fR, \fB\-\-query\fR
Query the local package database.
.RS
.TP
\fB\-Qi\fR \fIpkg\fR
Show detailed package information.
.TP
\fB\-Ql\fR \fIpkg\fR
List files owned by a package.
.TP
\fB\-Qs\fR \fIregex\fR
Search installed packages by name or description.
.TP
\fB\-Qo\fR \fIfile\fR
Find which package owns a file.
.TP
\fB\-Qk\fR \fIpkg\fR
Check that all files in a package exist on disk.
.TP
\fB\-Qkk\fR \fIpkg\fR
Verbose file check.
.TP
\fB\-Qe\fR
List explicitly installed packages.
.TP
\fB\-Qd\fR
List packages installed as dependencies.
.TP
\fB\-Qt\fR
List unrequired packages (not depended on by others).
.RE

.TP
\fB\-S\fR, \fB\-\-sync\fR
Synchronize package databases and install packages.
.RS
.TP
\fB\-Sy\fR
Refresh package databases.
.TP
\fB\-Syy\fR
Force refresh (even if up to date).
.TP
\fB\-Ss\fR \fIregex\fR
Search sync databases.  Long form: \fB\-\-search\fR.
.TP
\fB\-Si\fR \fIpkg\fR
Show remote package information.
.TP
\fB\-Sl\fR [\fIrepo\fR]
List packages in sync databases.
.TP
\fB\-Su\fR
Upgrade all installed packages.  Long form: \fB\-\-sysupgrade\fR.
.TP
\fB\-Suu\fR
Upgrade allowing downgrades.
.TP
\fB\-Sc\fR
Clean package cache (keep installed versions).
.TP
\fB\-Scc\fR
Clean all cached packages.
.TP
\fB\-\-needed\fR
Skip reinstalling packages already at the same version when using
\fB\-S\fR with explicit targets.  System upgrades (\fB\-Su\fR) always
skip same-version packages regardless of this flag (matching pacman).
Also respected by \fB\-\-libs\fR and \fB\-\-extreme\-libs\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-parallel\fR=\fIN\fR
Set the number of concurrent download streams.  Overrides the
\fBParallelDownloads\fR config value.  Default: 3.
.TP
\fB\-\-asdeps\fR
Install as dependency.
.TP
\fB\-\-asexplicit\fR
Install as explicitly requested.
.RE

.TP
\fB\-R\fR, \fB\-\-remove\fR
Remove packages.
.RS
.TP
\fB\-Rs\fR
Remove with unneeded dependencies.
.TP
\fB\-Rss\fR
Remove with ALL dependencies (including explicitly installed ones).
.TP
\fB\-Rc\fR
Cascade: remove packages depending on targets.
.TP
\fB\-Rn\fR
No .pacsave backups for modified config files.
.TP
\fB\-Ru\fR
Remove unneeded orphans.
.TP
\fB\-Rd\fR
Skip dependency version checks.
.TP
\fB\-Rdd\fR
Skip ALL dependency checks.
.TP
\fB\-\-print\fR
Dry-run: show what would be removed.  Skips lock acquisition and
confirmation prompts automatically.
.TP
\fB\-\-dbonly\fR
Only remove database entry, keep files on disk.  Implies
\fB\-\-noscriptlet\fR (install scripts are not run).
.TP
\fB\-\-noscriptlet\fR
Do not run install scriptlets during package operations.

.TP
\fB\-U\fR, \fB\-\-upgrade\fR
Install or upgrade from a local package file.
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-asdeps\fR
Install as a dependency.
.TP
\fB\-\-asexplicit\fR
Install as explicitly requested.
.TP
\fB\-w\fR
Download only, do not install.
.TP
\fB\-\-overwrite\fR \fIglob\fR
Allow overwriting files matching the glob pattern.
.RE

.TP
\fB\-D\fR, \fB\-\-database\fR
Modify the local package database.
.RS
.TP
\fB\-Dk\fR
Check database consistency (missing deps, file conflicts).
.TP
\fB\-Dkk\fR
Verbose database check.
.TP
\fB\-\-asdeps\fR \fIpkg\fR
Mark package as installed as a dependency.
.TP
\fB\-\-asexplicit\fR \fIpkg\fR
Mark package as explicitly installed.
.RE

.TP
\fB\-T\fR, \fB\-\-deptest\fR
Check dependency satisfiability.
.RS
.TP
\fB\-T\fR \fIdep1\fR [\fIdep2\fR ...]
Print any unsatisfied dependencies, exit 127 if any.
.RE

.TP
\fB\-F\fR, \fB\-\-files\fR
Query the files database.
.RS
.TP
\fB\-Fl\fR \fIpkg\fR
List files owned by remote packages.
.TP
\fB\-Fy\fR
Refresh files databases (downloads .files DBs).
.TP
\fB\-Fx\fR \fIregex\fR
Search using extended regex.
.TP
\fB\-\-machinereadable\fR
Null-delimited output for scripting.
.RE

.SH ACE-SPECIFIC OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-pacman\fR
Use pacman-compatible paths (/etc/pacman.conf, /var/lib/pacman/, etc).
This allows ace and pacman to share the same installed-package database.
.TP
\fB\-\-transfer\fR
One-shot migration: copy all pacman data (local DB, sync DBs, config,
cache, hooks, GPG keyring, log) into ace's native directories under
/var/lib/ace/. Idempotent and non-destructive.
.TP
\fB\-\-deptree\fR \fIpkg\fR
Display a recursive dependency tree for an installed package.  Shows
architecture, install reason (explicit/auto), version constraints,
satisfaction status, and separate subtrees for required, optional, and
build-time dependencies.  Similar to pactree(1) and zypper(8).
.TP
\fB\-\-history\fR
Display human-readable transaction history from the log file.
Colour-coded markers: green [INSTALL], yellow [REMOVE], crimson [UPGRADE].
.TP
\fB\-\-all\-optional\fR
When installing, also install all optional dependencies alongside
the target package(s).  Also applies during system upgrades (\fB\-Su\fR)
to pull in optional dependencies for every upgraded package.
.TP
\fB\-\-libs\fR
Check library-level dependencies for all packages being installed and
automatically mark packages that provide needed shared libraries.
Uses the sync database \fB%PROVIDES%\fR metadata to build a library-to-package
reverse index and resolve implicit provider relationships.  Results are cached
at \fI{dbpath}/cache/libcheck_cache\fR for speed on subsequent runs; the cache
is invalidated when sync databases are refreshed (\fB\-Sy\fR).  Prioritises
speed over exhaustive accuracy.
.TP
\fB\-\-extreme\-libs\fR
Cross-reference library needs against the system's \fBldconfig\fR(8) cache.
Shells out to \fBldconfig -p\fR to discover installed libraries, then
matches them against sync database provides to find missing providers.
Always runs fresh (bypasses the \fB\-\-libs\fR cache) for maximum accuracy
regardless of speed.  Reflects only the current system state; not suitable
for chroot or \fB\-\-root\fR operations on different systems.
.TP
\fB\-\-keyring\-init\fR
Initialize a fresh GPG keyring at the configured GPGDir. Creates the
directory, trust database, and an ACE master signing key.
.TP
\fB\-\-keyring\-populate\fR \fIname\fR
Import trusted keys from a keyring package into the configured GPG
directory. Equivalent to \fBpacman-key \-\-populate\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-debug\fR[\fB=\fIN\fR]
Enable debug output. Level 1 shows DB loading, resolution, and install
summary. Level 2 adds per-file extraction logging.
.TP
\fB\-\-config\fR \fIpath\fR
Use an alternate configuration file (default: /etc/ace.conf).
.TP
\fB\-\-root\fR \fIpath\fR
Set an alternate installation root.
.TP
\fB\-\-dbpath\fR \fIpath\fR
Set an alternate database path.
.TP
\fB\-\-noconfirm\fR
Skip all confirmation prompts.
.TP
\fB\-\-cachedir\fR \fIdir\fR
Set an alternate package cache directory (may be repeated).
.TP
\fB\-\-logfile\fR \fIpath\fR
Set an alternate log file path.
.TP
\fB\-\-sysupgrade\fR
Long form of \fB\-Su\fR: upgrade all installed packages.  Repeat for \fB\-Suu\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-search\fR
Long form of \fB\-Ss\fR: search sync databases.  The search term is taken
from positional arguments.
.TP
\fB\-\-ignoregroup\fR \fIgroup\fR
Ignore a package group during upgrades (repeatable).  Overrides any
\fBIgnoreGroup\fR entries in the configuration file.
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR \fIwhen\fR
Control coloured output: \fBauto\fR (default), \fBnever\fR, or \fBalways\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-noprogressbar\fR
Suppress progress bars during package extraction.
.TP
\fB\-\-disable\-download\-timeout\fR
Disable download timeouts for slow connections.
.TP
\fB\-\-disable\-sandbox\fR
Disable download sandboxing.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Install a package from repositories:
.RS
# ace -S neovim
.RE
.TP
Full system upgrade:
.RS
# ace -Syu
.RE
.TP
Search for a package:
.RS
ace -Ss "terminal emulator"
.RE
.TP
Show package information:
.RS
ace -Qi glibc
.RE
.TP
List files owned by a package:
.RS
ace -Ql firefox
.RE
.TP
Remove a package and its unneeded dependencies:
.RS
# ace -Rsn firefox
.RE
.TP
Install from a local package file:
.RS
# ace -U /path/to/pkg.pkg.tar.zst
.RE
.TP
Check database consistency:
.RS
ace -Dk
.RE
.TP
Dependency tree:
.RS
ace --deptree zsh
.RE
.TP
Transaction history:
.RS
ace --history
.RE
.TP
Migrate from pacman:
.RS
# ace --transfer
ace -Syu
.RE
.TP
Initialize keyring:
.RS
# ace --keyring-init
# ace --keyring-populate archlinux
.RE
.TP
Create a chroot:
.RS
mkdir -p /mnt/arch/var/lib/ace/local
echo 9 > /mnt/arch/var/lib/ace/local/ALPM_DB_VERSION
cp /var/lib/ace/sync/*.db /mnt/arch/var/lib/ace/sync/
# ace --config /etc/ace.conf --root /mnt/arch -S base linux vim
.RE

.SH HOOKS
Ace runs pre-transaction hooks before installation begins and post-transaction
hooks after every install (\fB\-S\fR, \fB\-U\fR) and remove (\fB\-R\fR) operation.
In addition, per-package post-install hooks fire after each individual package
is successfully extracted. Hooks are defined as
.B .hook
files in the configured
.B HookDir
(default:
.IR /etc/ace/hooks/ ).
.PP
Hook files use the standard ALPM format:
.PP
.nf
[Trigger]
Type = Package
Operation = Install
Operation = Upgrade
Target = linux

[Action]
When = PostTransaction
Exec = /usr/bin/mkinitcpio -P
.fi
.PP
Both
.B PreTransaction
and
.B PostTransaction
hooks are supported. Hooks with
.B AbortOnFail
set to true will cancel the transaction if they fail during PreTransaction.
PostTransaction failures are non-fatal.

.SH KEYRING
Ace manages its own GPG keyring for package signature verification.
.PP
Initialize a fresh keyring:
.RS
# ace --keyring-init
.RE
.PP
Import trusted keys from a keyring package:
.RS
# ace --keyring-populate archlinux
# ace --keyring-populate arcturus
.RE
.PP
The keyring is stored at the configured
.B GPGDir
(default:
.IR /etc/ace/gnupg/ ).

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/ace.conf
Default configuration file.
.TP
.I /var/lib/ace/local/
Local package database (native mode).
.TP
.I /var/lib/ace/sync/
Synchronized repository databases (native mode).
.TP
.I /var/lib/pacman/local/
Local package database (--pacman mode).
.TP
.I {dbpath}/cache/libcheck_cache
Library dependency resolution cache (--libs).  Stale entries are
automatically invalidated when sync databases are refreshed.
.TP
.I /var/log/ace.log
Transaction log.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ace.conf (5),
.BR pacman (8),
.BR pactree (1),
.BR pacman-key (8),
.BR gpg (1)

.SH BUGS
Report issues at the project repository. Known limitations: CachyOS
repositories lack %DEPENDS% metadata in sync databases; use official
Arch repositories for complete dependency resolution.
